column18: 07/28/2010: An explosion struck the Japanese oil tanker M Star shortly after midnight while it was passing through the Strait of Hormuz en route to Fujairah, United Arab Emirates. Initial reports were mixed regarding the cause of the explosion, which injured one person and dented the ship's hull but did not cause major damage. The Abdullah Azzam Brigades claimed responsibility for the explosion on jihadist websites, and authorities confirmed the presence of homemade explosives on the hull of the ship suggesting it was attacked using an explosives-laden vessel.
column64: The group claimed that the attack was in retaliation for the imprisonment in the US of Omar Abdel Rahman.
column97: An explosives-laden vessel was used in the attack.
column108: The explosion caused a large dent in the hull of the ship, caused damage to the hatches, and blew a lifeboat off the ship. No oil leaked from the ship.

column18: 09/07/2013: An explosive device detonated targeting a police patrol in Al-Quraya area, Fujairah emirate, United Arab Emirates. No casualties were reported. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
column97: A homemade roadside bomb was used in the attack.
